modules.description: This module defines configuration data for package installations, including OCaml versions and package lists with associated directives. It provides predefined values for common installation scenarios, such as global installation and compilation. These values are used to configure and select packages based on version constraints and installation contexts.

This module manages configuration data for package installations, supporting operations to define and select OCaml versions and package lists with version constraints. It works with custom data structures representing installation contexts and package directives. Concrete use cases include setting up global installations and configuring package selections during compilation.
